Given that Pt-C bonds are also formed during the preparation of catalysts, we construct six other models as counterparts to illustrate the influence of C atoms on HER performance when they are bonded with the Pt species (Fig. S27). Besides, the Pt species are anchored by the surface O atoms for these models without Ti vacancies. As shown in Fig. S28a, Ti3-xCNO2-C-PtC exhibits the best Gibbs free energies (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
